#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:6
msgid "Summary"
msgstr "摘要"

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:10
msgid ""
"Grammar of the Rust language should not be rustc implementation-defined. We "
"have a formal grammar at [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/"
"tree/master/src/grammar) which is to be used as the canonical and formal "
"representation of the Rust language."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:14
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr "動機"

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:20
msgid ""
"In many RFCs proposing syntactic changes ([\\#1228](https://github.com/rust-"
"lang/rfcs/blob/master/text/1228-placement-left-arrow.md), [\\#1219](https://"
"github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/blob/master/text/1219-use-group-as.md) and "
"[\\#1192](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/blob/master/text/1192-inclusive-"
"ranges.md) being some of more recently merged RFCs) the changes are "
"described rather informally and are hard to both implement and discuss which "
"also leads to discussions containing a lot of guess-work."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:24
msgid ""
"Making [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/"
"grammar) to be the canonical grammar and demanding for description of "
"syntactic changes to be presented in terms of changes to the formal grammar "
"should greatly simplify both the discussion and implementation of the RFCs. "
"Using a formal grammar also allows us to discover and rule out existence of "
"various issues with the grammar changes (e.g. grammar ambiguities) during "
"design phase rather than implementation phase or, even worse, after the "
"stabilisation."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:30
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr "詳細設計"

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:34
msgid ""
"Sadly, the [grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/"
"grammar) in question is [not quite equivalent](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"rust/issues?utf8=✓&q=is:issue+is:open+label:A-grammar) to the implementation "
"in rustc yet. We cannot possibly hope to catch all the quirks in the rustc "
"parser implementation, therefore something else needs to be done."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:38
msgid ""
"This RFC proposes following approach to making [src/grammar](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) the canonical Rust language "
"grammar:"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:40
msgid ""
"Fix the already known discrepancies between implementation and [src/grammar]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar);"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:41
msgid ""
"Make [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/"
"grammar) a [semi-canonical grammar](#semi-canonical-grammar);"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:42
msgid ""
"After a period of time transition [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"rust/tree/master/src/grammar) to a [fully-canonical grammar](#fully-"
"canonical-grammar)."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:44
msgid "Semi-canonical grammar"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:47
msgid ""
"Once all known discrepancies between the [src/grammar](https://github.com/"
"rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) and rustc parser implementation are "
"resolved, [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/"
"grammar) enters the state of being semi-canonical grammar of the Rust "
"language."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:50
msgid ""
"Semi-canonical means that all new development involving syntax changes are "
"made and discussed in terms of changes to the [src/grammar](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) and [src/grammar](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) is in general regarded to as the "
"canonical grammar except when new discrepancies are discovered. These "
"discrepancies must be swiftly resolved, but resolution will depend on what "
"kind of discrepancy it is:"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:55
msgid ""
"For syntax changes/additions introduced after [src/grammar](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) gained the semi-canonical state, "
"the [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) "
"is canonical;"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:57
msgid ""
"For syntax that was present before [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-"
"lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) gained the semi-canonical state, in most "
"cases the implementation is canonical."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:60
msgid ""
"This process is sure to become ambiguous over time as syntax is increasingly "
"adjusted (it is harder to “blame” syntax changes compared to syntax "
"additions), therefore the resolution process of discrepancies will also "
"depend more on a decision from the Rust team."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:64
msgid "Fully-canonical grammar"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:67
msgid ""
"After some time passes, [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/"
"master/src/grammar) will transition to the state of fully canonical grammar. "
"After [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/"
"grammar) transitions into this state, for any discovered discrepancies the "
"rustc parser implementation must be adjusted to match the [src/grammar]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar), unless decided "
"otherwise by the RFC process."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:72
msgid "RFC process changes for syntactic changes and additions"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:74
msgid ""
"Once the [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/"
"grammar) enters semi-canonical state, all RFCs must describe syntax "
"additions and changes in terms of the formal [src/grammar](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar). Discussion about these changes "
"are also expected (but not necessarily will) to become more formal and "
"easier to follow."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:78
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:81
msgid ""
"This RFC introduces a period of ambiguity during which neither "
"implementation nor [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/"
"master/src/grammar) are truly canonical representation of the Rust language. "
"This will be less of an issue over time as discrepancies are resolved, but "
"its an issue nevertheless."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:85
msgid "Alternatives"
msgstr "替代方案"

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:88
msgid ""
"One alternative would be to immediately make [src/grammar](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/grammar) a fully-canonical grammar of the "
"Rust language at some arbitrary point in the future."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:91
msgid ""
"Another alternative is to simply forget idea of having a formal grammar be "
"the canonical grammar of the Rust language."
msgstr ""

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:94
msgid "Unresolved questions"
msgstr "未解決的問題"

#: src/1331-grammar-is-canonical.md:97
msgid ""
"How much time should pass between [src/grammar](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"rust/tree/master/src/grammar) becoming semi-canonical and fully-canonical?"
msgstr ""
